			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This issue is more a reminder to check that the 4 (or maybe only 3) models of TLS are supported in the ARM port of glibc. I say 3 because there is a TODO in LLVM to support Local Dynamic. We will need General Dynamic to support dlopen.

This is also a reminder to remove a hack (http://codereview.chromium.org/5049002/) that forces LLVM to generate Initial Exec in PIC mode (added to test). This is because LLVM does not expose an option like gcc's &amp;quot;-ftls-model=model&amp;quot;.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-10-25T18:09:50.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-11-15T23:17:33.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Assigned</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
